   "source": [
    "## Phase 6: PGBM Scenarios + SPO+ Neural Net Point Forecast\n",
    "\n",
    "**Idea:** Combine the best of Phase 2/4/5 (PGBM uncertainty quantification) with Phase 3 (SPO+ predict-then-optimize loss). A lightweight neural net is trained with the SPO+ surrogate loss, but the LP oracle uses *PGBM-sampled scenarios* (rather than Gaussian-perturbed true load) for the stochastic DC-OPF during training. At evaluation time, the SPO+-tuned NN provides the point forecast while PGBM supplies the scenario distribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Train SPO+ NN with PGBM scenarios as the uncertainty context (mirrors Phase 3 setup but replaces KNN-bootstrap with PGBM quantile scenarios)\n",
    "2. Run the PtO evaluation loop: NN point forecast + PGBM scenarios → stochastic DC-OPF\n",
    "3. Compare head-to-head against all prior phases"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "546bc026",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.1 Train SPO+ Neural Net Using PGBM Scenarios"
   ]
  },
  {
